# RDIS Deployment Guide

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+ with npm
- Git for version control
- VS Code with Claude Code extension
- Administrative access to modify hook scripts

## Installation Steps

### 1. System Setup
```bash
# Verify Node.js version
node --version  # Should be 18+

# Install dependencies
npm install -g typescript ts-node

# Verify Claude Code environment
ls -la .claude/
```

### 2. RDIS Module Installation
```bash
# Create RDIS directory structure
./scripts/setup-rdis-structure.sh

# Install RDIS dependencies
cd modules/rdis
npm install

# Configure RDIS settings
cp config/rdis.example.json config/rdis.json
# Edit config/rdis.json with your settings
```

### 3. Hook Integration
```bash
# Backup existing hooks
cp .claude/hooks/post-tool-use.sh .claude/hooks/post-tool-use.sh.backup
cp .claude/hooks/session-start.sh .claude/hooks/session-start.sh.backup

# Install enhanced hooks
cp modules/rdis/integration/hooks/* .claude/hooks/

# Make hooks executable
chmod +x .claude/hooks/*.sh
```

### 4. Command Registration
```bash
# Install RDIS commands
cp modules/rdis/integration/commands/* .claude/commands/

# Verify command installation
ls -la .claude/commands/
```

### 5. Template Integration
```bash
# Install RDIS template builders
cp modules/rdis/templates/builders/* modules/templates/builders/

# Update variable substitution engine
cp modules/rdis/integration/engines/* modules/engines/
```

## Configuration

